      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis is missing the original patch which introduced test_61b, and renamed test_61 to test_61a.  That was patch a8f4d1e5fd79 (\"LU-11403 llite: ll_fault fixes\"), which doesn't appear to be backported yet.\n\nThis patch should probably get a label:\n\n Fixes: a8f4d1e5fd79 (\"LU-11403 llite: ll_fault fixes\")\n\nto make this more clear.  I don't think it is harmful to add this to the commit message in only the b2_12 backport, even though it should have been in the original.  That would have made it much more clear that this patch is not useful by itself.",
